{{Expand French|topic=culture|date=February 2010|Georges Azéma}}
'''Georges Azéma''' (died May 9, 1864) was a [[France|French]] historian from [[Réunion]].  Son of the writer [[Étienne Azéma]] and brother to the doctor [[Mazaé Azéma]], his son [[Henri Azéma|Henri]] was also a doctor; his grandfather [[Jean-Baptiste Azéma]] had briefly served as [[governor of Réunion]]; other relatives include the poet [[Jean-Henri Azéma]] and the historian [[Jean-Pierre Azéma]].

