The '''Prix Marcel Pollitzer''', formally the '''Prix des écrivains combattants Fondation Marcel Pollitzer''', is a [[France|French]] [[literary award]] created in 1953 by the [[Association des écrivains combattants]]. Named for writer [[Marcel Pollitzer]], it is awarded every year to "a work of history and, preferably, to a biography".<ref>[http://www.lesecrivainscombattants.org/Prix-litteraires.htm Prix Littéraires<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
