'''Thomas William Downes''' (18 February 1868 &ndash; 6 August 1938) was a New Zealand historian, ethnologist and river works supervisor. He was born in [[Wellington]], [[Wellington]], [[New Zealand]] on 18 February 1868.<ref name="DNZB Downes">{{DNZB|title=Thomas William Downes|first= Arthur P.|last= Bates|id=3d15|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

